<!doctype html>
<meta charset="utf8">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./spec.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/8.4/styles/github.min.css">
<script src="./spec.js"></script>
<pre class="metadata">
title: MaybeDeferredResolvePromise (name TBD)
stage: 1
contributors: Matthew Gaudet
</pre>

<emu-clause id="sec-safe-resolve-promise">
  <h1>MaybeDeferredPromiseResolve Abstract Operations</h1>

  <p>These operations provide a mechanism for resolving promises without risk of synchronously executing arbitrary user code. When the resolution value is an object that could trigger user code (such as a Proxy, a thenable, or an object with accessor properties), the actual resolution is deferred to a future job.</p>

  <emu-clause id="sec-requires-deferred-promise-resolution" type="abstract operation">
    <h1>
      RequiresDeferredPromiseResolution (
        _value_: an ECMAScript language value,
      ): either a normal completion containing a Boolean or a throw completion
    </h1>
    <dl class="header">
      <dt>description</dt>
      <dd>It determines whether resolving a promise with _value_ might execute user code that should be deferred to avoid running user code</dd>
    </dl>
    <emu-alg>
      1. Let _o_ be _value_.
      1. While _o_ is defined, Repeat:
        1. If _value_ is not an Object, return *false*.
        1. If _value_ has a [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot, return *true*.
        1. Let _desc_ be _o_.[[GetOwnProperty]](*"then"*).
        1. If _desc_ is not *undefined* and IsAccessorDescriptor(_desc_) is *true*, return *true*.
        1. Set _o_ to _o_.[[GetPrototypeOf]]().
      1. Let _constructorDesc_ be ? _value_.[[GetOwnProperty]](*"constructor"*).
      1. If _constructorDesc_ is not *undefined*, then
        1. If IsAccessorDescriptor(_constructorDesc_) is *true*, return *true*.
      1. Return *false*.
    </emu-alg>
    <emu-note>
      <p>I've sketched this asuming that [[GetPrototypeOf]] cannot trap on a getter, but I'm not 100% sure of this</p>
    </emu-note>
  </emu-clause>

  <emu-clause id="sec-new-deferred-safe-resolve-job" type="abstract operation">
    <h1>
      NewDeferredSafeResolveJob (
        _promiseToResolve_: a Promise,
        _resolution_: an ECMAScript language value,
        _realm_: a Realm Record,
      ): a Record with fields [[Job]] (a Job Abstract Closure) and [[Realm]] (a Realm Record)
    </h1>
    <dl class="header">
      <dt>description</dt>
      <dd>It returns a Job that performs deferred promise resolution in a microtask.</dd>
    </dl>
    <emu-alg>
      1. Let _job_ be a new Job Abstract Closure with no parameters that captures _promiseToResolve_ and _resolution_ and performs the following steps when called:
        1. Return ? PromiseResolve(_promiseToResolve_, _resolution_).
      1. Return the Record { [[Job]]: _job_, [[Realm]]: _realm_ }.
    </emu-alg>
  </emu-clause>

  <emu-clause id="sec-safe-resolve-promise-operation" type="abstract operation">
    <h1>
      MaybeDeferredPromiseResolve (
        _promise_: a Promise,
        _resolution_: an ECMAScript language value,
      ): either a normal completion containing *undefined* or a throw completion
    </h1>
    <dl class="header">
      <dt>description</dt>
      <dd>It resolves _promise_ with _resolution_, deferring to a microtask if _resolution_ might execute user code.</dd>
    </dl>
    <emu-alg>
      1. Assert: _promise_ is a Promise.
      1. Assert: _promise_.[[PromiseState]] is ~pending~.
      1. Let _requiresDeferred_ be ? RequiresDeferredPromiseResolution(_resolution_).
      1. If _requiresDeferred_ is *true*, then
        1. Set _promise_.[[PromiseState]] to ~deferred~.
        1. Let _callerRealm_ be the current Realm Record.
        1. Let _job_ be NewDeferredSafeResolveJob(_promise_, _resolution_, _callerRealm_).
        1. Perform HostEnqueuePromiseJob(_job_.[[Job]], _job_.[[Realm]]).
        1. Return *undefined*.
      1. Return ? PromiseResolve(_promise_, _resolution_).
    </emu-alg>
    <emu-note>
      <p>~deffered~ is a new state that I've not run through the rest of the spec, but the intention is that it prevents future resolutions from overriding the resolution applied here. </p>
    </emu-note>
  </emu-clause>
</emu-clause>
